{
  "texts": [
    "Ortiz et al. (2016) put out four distinct voting methods and two deep learning-based structures.",
    "They are put into practice and contrasted, yielding a robust classification architecture that computes discriminative features in an unsupervised manner.",
    "Generally speaking, a combination of weak classifiers is more accurate than a single classifier.",
    "The suggested approach exhibits strong performance in testing for more complex cases of MCI subject classification due to the integration of two techniques.",
    "It is valid for distinguishing between NC and AD images."
  ]
}